<title>A Healthy Morning for You and Your Blog</title>
<link>http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/SiteSketch101/~3/nBGthk8k0SY/</link>
<comments>http://www.sitesketch101.com/a-healthy-morning-for-you-and-your-blog/#comments</comments>
<pubDate>Thu, 01 Sep 2011 04:00:40 +0000</pubDate>
<dc:creator>Brandi Starr</dc:creator>
<category><![CDATA[Commanding Influence]]></category>
<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.sitesketch101.com/?p=14316</guid>
<description><![CDATA[Backlinks (other pages on the web that link to your website or blog) are extremely important to your search engine optimization and search marketing strategy. A key part of search&#8230;]]></description>
<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Backlinks (other pages on the web that link to your website or blog) are extremely important to your search engine optimization and search marketing strategy. A key part of search algorithms includes checking the number of backlinks and their sources to determine the sites importance. Therefore it is important to not only create backlinks to your site but to also have relevant sites linking to yours.</p>
<p>In addition to the SEO and SEM benefits, when your site appears on another site you then receive traffic from visitors of the linking site. When those links appear on related sites you already know the person has an interest in your particular subject matter.</p>
<p>There are tons of methods (and scams) that people use to create lots of backlinks and traffic to their sites. One simple approach that has become a key part of my backlinking strategy is to comment on blogs and discussion forums regularly.</p>
<p>I’ve recently become a tea drinker, tea has amazing healing properties and health benefits in an 8 oz of cup of yummy deliciousness. I start my morning off with a hot cup of a kamiya papaya oolong and silver needle white tea blend which gives my body antioxidants, improves my skin, speeds my metabolism, and has anti-aging properties among other things.</p>
<p>Not only does my morning routine provide health benefits for my body, I couple my cup of tea with my RSS feed making it a healthy morning for my website and my business as well. Here’s my routine and how using it can benefit your business as well:</p>
<h3>Follow Blogs &amp; Forums Relevant to Your Target Audience</h3>
<p>I follow twelve or so blogs that share content around marketing, social media, SEO, content management, consulting, and other subjects that are relevant to my target audience. You want to choose enough sources that you have a variety of content to read and share, but not so many that you never have time to read them. You also want to choose sources that post regularly and have a solid following.</p>
<h3>Read &amp; Reply to Add Value</h3>
<p>Spend 15-20 minutes each morning (which is the amount of time it takes to enjoy a cup of tea) reading the blogs and forums that you’ve selected to follow. As you are reading if you have feedback, additional information to add, or questions for the author add your responses and include the link to your website.</p>
<p>The key here is to add value by include something more than “great post”. Approach it as you would a business conversation, you interject when you have something to say that adds to the discussion and not just to hear yourself speak. Also, be courteous; the comments section of another writers blog is not the place to self-promote.</p>
<h3>Share the Post with Your Networks</h3>
<p>Because you found the post of great value and have contributed to the discussion you want to make sure to share the resource with your social networks. Most blogs and forums have share buttons within the post that allow you to easily share the resource with others. This not only gives you additional content to share with your followers but furthers establishes you as an expert in your field who stays abreast of relevant topics and discussions.</p>
<h3>Measure the Response</h3>
<p>As with any marketing effort it is important to measure your results. My choice tools for measuring my linking strategy is using <a href="https://www.google.com/webmasters/tools/">Google Webmaster Tools</a> and <a href="http://www.google.com/analytics/">Google Analytics</a>.</p>
<p>Through the “Links to your site” section of Google Webmaster Tools you can view sites linking to yours and how many incoming links they are creating. These are updated periodically and not in real time so it may take some time for this section to populate.</p>
<p>However, if over time you have commented on sites repeatedly and they aren’t showing up you may want to choose other sites to be more active on. The Google Analytics “Referral Traffic” report also shows web traffic that was referred to you from other sites. This allows you to see how much traffic each site is sending to yours to assess which blogs and forums you should be most active on. Together these tools allow you to achieve the greatest results from your efforts.</p>
<p>So tomorrow morning grab a cup of tea, log into your favorite RSS reader and give your SEO strategy a boost through effective link building.</p>
